[SN]TITLE[SN]
Sean Rigg death: Policeman in court on perjury charge

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
A police sergeant accused of lying at the 2012 inquest into the death of a man in custody has appeared at Westminster Magistrates' Court.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
Sean Rigg, a 40-year-old musician from south London, died of a cardiac arrest while he was being held at Brixton police station on 21 August 2008.
The officer, on restricted duties, did not enter a plea to the perjury charge.
He was ordered to appear at Southwark Crown Court on 22 September for a preliminary hearing.
Mr Rigg, who suffered from schizophrenia, had been arrested on suspicion of attacking a man in Balham, south London.
